## Calendar Invitations

### Best Practices for Calendar Invites
- **Clear title**: "1:1 - [Your Name] & [Their Name] - [Purpose]"
- **Detailed description**: Include agenda, preparation needed, and call-in info
- **Attachments**: Add relevant documents or previous notes
- **Reminders**: Set appropriate reminders (15 min for virtual, 1 hour for in-person)
- **Location**: Specify exact room or virtual meeting link

### Sample Calendar Description
```
1:1 Meeting: [Purpose/Context]

Agenda:
- [Topic 1]
- [Topic 2]
- [Topic 3]

Preparation:
- [Any pre-reading or preparation needed]

Call-in Information:
- [Meeting link]
- [Phone number if applicable]

Duration: [X minutes]
```

## Follow-up Tips
- Send invitations 3-5 days in advance for regular meetings
- Send 1-2 weeks in advance for casual/social meetings
- Always include 2-3 time options
- Follow up within 24 hours if no response
- Confirm attendance 24 hours before the meeting
